<P>
   (UNDATED) _ Bill Clinton's tour of South Asia that got under way
Monday marks the first visit by a U.S. president to India and
Pakistan in more than 20 and 30 years respectively. In that sense
alone, the trip is historic. In addition, however, this represents
an important moment where a powerful outsider can play a role in
nudging the two nuclear weapon-wielding countries towards a kind of
sanity...By The Editorial Board of The Independent &QL;
