   &UR; POPE ARRIVES IN THE LAND OF CHRIST _ AND CONTROVERSY &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; POPE-HOLYLAND-400&AMP;add-INDEPENDENT &QL;
</P>
<P>
   JERUSALEM _ Pope John Paul II touched down in Jordan Monday to
begin the most ambitious and diplomatically perilous journey of his
22-year papacy, and at once made clear that he would not shy away
from the combustible issues of Middle East politics. Although on a
personal (and long dreamed of) spiritual mission to the land of
Christ and Moses, the pope also does not intend to be blind to the
issues that have so hopelessly divided the region...By Phil Reeves,
The Independent &QL;
