<P>
   &UR; INDIA'S HIGH-TECH BOOM IS GREAT SUCCESS STORY &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INDIA-HITECH-BOOM-INDEPENDENT &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   LONDON _ The Indian high-tech boom is one of the great
under-publicized stories of the world economy. For many years the
Indian subcontinent has produced talented computer people who have
headed off to the developed world to make their fortunes. Silicon
Valley in California is attracting upwards of 50,000 of them a
year. And last year, Indian software exports were nearly $3 billion
_ ten times the level of four years earlier....By Hamish McRae, The
Independent of London &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Moved Feb. 23, 2000) &QL;
</P>
