<HEADLINE>
WINE OF THE WEEK 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  (For release Friday, March 24, 2000) 
 
By MICHAEL LONSFORD 
c. 2000 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   On this date in 1874, the great magician Harry Houdini was born.
He was a native of what country?
</P>
<P>
   One of the great wines of the world is vintage port, but it can
get expensive. But, magically it seems, you can get most of the
pleasure for a fraction of the cost with a vintage-character port,
such as the 1994 Taylor ``Late Bottled Vintage'' Port _ 4 stars _
with lush, cassis-and-chocolate undertones. And it manages to
balance its sweetness with good acidity, a high-wire act not all
ports can boast of.
</P>
<P>
   And when you pay for it, less than $20 will disappear.
</P>
<P>
   _ Houdini was born in Budapest, Hungary. He died on Halloween,
1926.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
