<HEADLINE>
THE SURF CAMP EXPERIENCE 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  (Eds.: Photo available on NYT database) 
 
By JOE DOGGETT 
c. 2000 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Adventurers eager to experience the thrills of a surf camp can
choose from several South Pacific locales and closer-to-home
destinations in Mexico and Central and South America.
</P>
<P>
   Prices vary depending on season, type of accommodations and
other factors but average $700-$1,000 for a one-week stay. This
includes lodging, meals, airport transfers and transportation to
surfing areas.
</P>
<P>
   Surfers normally are expected to bring their own gear.
</P>
<P>
   These are among surf camps or resorts in the Pacific:
</P>
<P>
   _ Namotu Blue Water Sports Resort, Namotu Island, Fiji: Weeklong
full-service packages with access to three reef-pass breaks. Call
WaterWays Surf Adventures at 800-928-3757 or 818-376-0341; fax
818-376-0353; e-mail waterways(at)waterwaystravel.com.
</P>
<P>
   _ Tavarua Island Resort, Tavarua Island, Fiji: Full-service
seven-day package trips with access by boat to several reef-pass
breaks, including private access to Cloudbreak, one of the finest
left-breaking waves in the world (experts only). Call Tavarua
Island Tours at 805-686-4551; fax 805-683-6696.
</P>
<P>
   _ Lalati Resort, Frigate's Pass, Fiji: Full-service trips (daily
rates available), first-class lodging and meals with access to
reef-pass surf at Frigate's Pass. Contact WaterWays Surf Adventures
(see Namotu).
</P>
<P>
   _ Good Sumateran Surf Charters, Mentawi Islands, Indonesia:
Full-service live-aboard charters to explore remote reef breaks.
One-week Grajagan trips available. Call 888-407-4663; access
www.surftraveler.com.
</P>
<P>
   _ Salani Surf Resort, Samoa: Full-service six-day package with
access to south-swell reef-pass surf. Contact WaterWays Surf
Adventures (see Namotu).
</P>
<P>
   _ Bobby's Grajagan Surf Camp, Grajagan, Java: Full-service trips
(three, six, nine or 13 nights) with front-door access to
Grajagan's world-class left reef break. Contact WaterWays Surf
Adventures (see Namotu).
</P>
<P>
   These surf camps are in Mexico or Central or South America:
</P>
<P>
   _ Playa Kandahar Surf Resort, north of Ixtapa/Zihuatanejo,
Mexico: Full-service package trips with access by boat or vehicle
to remote reef and point surf along the Pacific Coast. Call
760-631-7470; fax 760-724-4254; access www.playa-kandahar.com.
</P>
<P>
   _ Costa Azul Adventure Resort, north of Puerto Vallarta, Mexico:
Full-service surfing packages with optional Corky Carroll Surf
School; access to a variety of point, reef and beach breaks.
Contact 800-365-7613; access www.costaazul.com.
</P>
<P>
   _ Hotel Fuego del Sol, Jaco Beach, Costa Rica: Full-service
packages with vehicle transportation to reef and beach breaks;
surfing instructions available. Call 011-506-643-3737; access
www.fuegodelsol.com.
</P>
<P>
   _ Lohi Lani, Costa Rica: Sixty-foot sailing catamaran offers
six-day scheduled trips or private charters for wave exploration
along remote stretches of the Pacific Coast. Call 714-957-8144;
e-mail lohelani2(at)aol.com.
</P>
<P>
   _ Casablanca Surf Resort, Panama: Full-service seven-night
package trips to one of the most consistent spots in Central
America. Contact WaterWays Surf Adventures (see Namotu).
</P>
<P>
   _ Surf Express, Ecuador/northern Peru: Package trips with guides
and lodging for reef and point breaks during the south swell
season. Call 321-779-2124; access www.surfex.com.
</P>
<P>
   Not quite ready for camp? Another option is to travel to a surf
school to prepare for a bigger adventure. Among options:
</P>
<P>
   _ Nancy Emerson School of Surfing, Maui, Hawaii: Beginner and
intermediate surfing lessons. Call808-873-0264; e-mail
nce9(at)hotmail.com.
</P>
<P>
   _ Lou Maresca's Surf School, Costa Rica: Year-round surfing
instruction. Call 561-231-1044; access www.surfguru.com/surfschool.
</P>
<P>
   _ Surf Diva, La Jolla, Calif.: This is billed as the ``first
all-girl surf school.'' Summer camp available with instructors Izzy
Tihanyi, Shyna Ellis and Heather McDonald. Call 858-454-8273;
access www.surfdiva.com.
</P>
<P>
