<P>
   ALZHEIMERS _ WASHINGTON _ As the baby boom generation ages, the
number of Alzheimer's patients could double within 30 years placing
enormous strains on the nation's health care programs including
Medicare, according to a report being released Tuesday. Report will
include state-by-state predictions on future Alzheimer's
populations. This report comes Maureen Reagan, daughter of
President Reagan, and others urge a Senate panel to earmark $100
million next year for Alzheimer's research. (Lipman, Cox News
Service). 15. WITH PHOTOS by Rick McKay.
