<P>
   SOCIAL-SECURITY _ WASHINGTON _ In what may be the only change to
the Social Security law this year, the Senate is expected to vote
today to repeal the ``earnings test'' which reduces benefits for
working seniors aged 65 to 69. The House already has passed the
bill and President Clinton has said he will sign it. The Senate
probably won't vote until late afternoon. (Lipman, Cox News
Service). 20.
</P>
