<P>
   GOP-LUNTZ _ WASHINGTON - After analyzing research from New
Hampshire, South Carolina and New York, Republican pollster Frank
Luntz has some advice for Gov. George W. Bush: wrap John McCain in
a big ``bear hug'' and don't let go. If Bush does not win
two-thirds of the McCain vote, Luntz warns, the presumptive GOP
presidential nominee will lose the White House to Vice President Al
Gore. Luntz, who polled for Ross Perot, says Gore is reaching out
to McCain voters the way Bill Clinton did to Perot voters in 1992.
But he says the Bush camp is criticizing McCain the way the
Republican Party leadership did Perot in 1992. (Shepard, Cox News
Service). 15.
</P>
