   WRESTLING GOES TO SCHOOL: ``Wrestling is theater for America's
masses,'' says Mike Burnette, longtime wrestling fan and technical
director of the Dunn Center at North Carolina Wesleyan College.
``It appeals to the basic human instinct. We're all violent by
nature _ that's why action movies are so popular.'' And at N.C.
Wesleyan, wrestling goes to school.
