<P>
   AFRICA'S AIDS ORPHANS: In sub-Saharan Africa, 23.3 million
people _ most of them women _ are infected with HIV/AIDS, compared
with less than 1 million in North America. Efforts to stop the
disease's progress have been largely futile. Few Africans can
afford treatments more readily available in the West, such as AZT.
The disease is destroying entire villages, but beyond that it is
robbing these countries of a whole generation of potentially
productive people. It has created more than 10 million orphans _ a
number that is expected to soar to 13 million next year.
</P>
