<P>
   COURT-SMOKING-SIDEBAR (Washington) _ The Food and Drug
Administration lacks the authority to regulate cigarettes, the
Supreme Court rules. But the agency still sets rules for many other
products, from bio-engineered corn and Viagra, to cosmetics,
pacemakers, breast implants, cellular phones and CD players. By
