routes. The flight attendants, who are waiting for a mandatory
30-day cooling off period to end at 12:01 a.m. Saturday, want to
maximize pressure on the company with a strategy they have dubbed
CHAOS _ Create Havoc Around Our System. In response, US Airways,
the nation's sixth-largest airline, plans to take an unusual step
of its own, saying that unless a contract is reached by Saturday,
it would suspend all its operations, rather than let the flight
attendants whipsaw the company and its customers. By Steven
Greenhouse.
