NYT-03-21-00 1754EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT20000321.0214 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-21 18:02 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A3768 &Cx1f; tad-z
r e BC-THEN-REVU-COX     03-21 0322
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-THEN-REVU-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    May-December pair make comic sparks
 &HT;    By Kevin D. Thompson
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Billie is a recently divorced, 33-year-old book editor. She
lives in a swank hotel after leaving her self-absorbed lawyer
hubby.
</P>
<P>
   Billie's (Susan Floyd) friends want to hook her up. Too late. In
walks the man, er, kid of her dreams. Aidan (Thomas Newton) is a
22-year-old room service waiter who looks like Doogie Howser's
twin. Both went to Northwestern, Billie learns.
</P>
<P>
   ``When did you graduate?'' she asks excitedly.
</P>
<P>
   ``May,'' is the reply.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't know if that totally freaks me out or kind of turns me
on,'' Billie wonders.
</P>
<P>
   Welcome to The Graduate _ TV style.
</P>
<P>
   Then Came You is a charming romantic comedy about the
complexities of a May-December romance. As Billie laments, Aidan is
all the right things in the wrong package. But, hey, the sex is
good. So, does it really matter that Aidan never heard of Mrs.
Robinson? Or that he pulls out a sad wad of dollar bills on a date?
Or that he doesn't remember the bicentennial? Or that he likes to
swim in Lake Michigan?
</P>
<P>
   Of course not. The sex is good.
</P>
<P>
   Then Came You, based on the real life of co-creator Betsy
Thomas, was originally scheduled to air in the fall. ABC, however,
didn't think it was ready for prime time. Well, Then Came You is
certainly funnier than the bland Two Girls and A Guy. Floyd and
Newton are instantly likable as the lovestruck couple. Floyd is
bundle of perky energy (think a dark-haired Nancy Travis) and
Newton is a wonderful mixture of wide-eyed innocence and heartfelt
sensitivity.
</P>
<P>
   While Miriam Shor and Desmond Askew are cardboard sitcom
sidekicks as Billie's and Aidan's best buddies, at least they don't
make you gag.
</P>
<P>
   And Then Came You should only make you laugh.
</P>
<P>
   kevinthompson(at)pbpost.com
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-03-21-00 1802EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
