 CHRON  
These are the stories The San Francisco Chronicle Food section
plans to move Tuesday, March 21, on the New York Times wire.
Questions? Please call Lesli Neilson at 415-777-8402. &HT;     
 
SAN FRANCISCO _  SUPPORTING  _ If the food world awarded Oscars to
ingredients, Best Supporting Flavor would be a critical category.
Like a good movie, a good dish depends just as much on its
supporting cast as it does on its star. Supporting flavors make
food interesting, bite after bite, giving a dish fullness and extra
verve. 
Main story with recipes. 
 By Robin Davis  
 c. 1999 The San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
SAN FRANCISCO _  &UR; BEARD CHEFS &LR;  _ Bay Area chefs, restaurateurs,
vintners, cookbook authors and local media have captured a wealth
of this year's James Beard Foundation nominations, which are
considered the Academy Awards of food.
<P>
   &UR; c. 1999 The San Francisco Chronicle &QL;  &LR; 
 &QL; 
SAN FRANCISCO _  &UR; SECRETS-UDON &LR;  _ Chef David Vardy has a unique
personal vision of East-West cooking at O Chame in Berkeley. While
he wouldn't claimto be a Japanese chef, his sensibilities are as
traditional as his top-level Tokyo counterparts. He's become known
for his noodle dishes, and what he creates is superior to any of
the noodle houses in San Francisco's Japantown.
</P>
<P>
   This is the latest installment of the regular column describing
what makes a Bay Area restaurant's dish a success, we'll tell how
to make it.
</P>
<P>
   With chef's secrets for success, recipe.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; By Michael Bauer &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; c. 1999 The San Francisco Chronicle &QL;  &LR; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
SAN FRANCISCO _  &UR; FOODNEWS &LR;  _ Northern California reaction to the
Clinton administration's proposed rules for organic food. Also,
bananas and soy.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; By Kim Severson &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; c. 1999 The San Francisco Chronicle &QL;  &LR; 
 &QL; 
SAN FRANCISCO _  &UR; WORKING &LR;  _ No matter the etymology of puttanesca,
the sound of the name is appropriate for such a spicy, zesty sauce,
making it perfect for a 30-Minute Main Dish when served with
linguine. It makes a very easy meal. Fast &AMP; Fresh: Salmon with
Leeks &AMP; Bok Choy; Now &AMP; Later: Black Bean Enchiladaswith Chipotle
Sauce.
</P>
<P>
