<P>
   HOMEDEPOT-FLOORING _ Home Depot announced today that it will
begin testing a flooring concept store starting in mid 2000. ``The
store will carry an expanded assortment in all categories of
flooring, accommodating customers from do-it-yourselfers to pros --
offering how-to clinics and pro quantities, as well as
installation,'' said Pedro Mendiguren, vice president of strategic
business development for The Home Depot. This could be a big blow
to independent flooring retailers and chains like Flooring America.
Home Depot has been hugely successful with its carpet and flooring
sales. The store's name and exact location will be announced at a
later date. (Bond, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   ONLINE-RETAILING _ Total System Services, the Columbus company
that processes 86 percent of the business visa and master cards in
the US, is moving into electronic payment processing. they are
forming dotsconnect.com, a wholly owned sub. that will try to be
the payment method for online retailing. (Clothier, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   DELTA-DESIGN _ For the second time in three years, Delta Air
Lines is changing the paint scheme on its planes. The airline is
switching to a swoopy red-and-blue stripe that runs the length of
the fuselage and up the tail. The new livery is part of a corporate
``re-branding'' that dovetails with a new ad campaign launched by
the carrier's new agency, Leo Burnett. The switch means that, for
the next few years, Delta will have three separate paint schemes
flying around, because it was only about halfway through a project
to replace its old '60s livery with a new design rolled out in
1997. Will have pic of latest livery, set to be rolled out publicly
tomorrow. (Thurston, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
