   CENTER, BELOW MAIN DISPLAY:
</P>
<P>
   FED-MARKETPLACE (New York) _ The no-surprises Federal Reserve
Board gave investors just what they were expecting on Tuesday: a
one-quarter point increase in short-term interest rates. The
full-of-surprises stock market delivered a smashing gain on the
news, with two of the broadest indexes closing at new highs. By
Gretchen Morgenson.
</P>
<P>
   (Will move by 8:30 p.m.)
