</P>
<P>
   POPE-ISRAEL (Jerusalem) _ Pope John Paul II arrives in Israel
after celebrating Mass for 40,000 at a packed sports stadium in
Jordan. By CECILE HOLMES and DEBORAH HORAN.
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-INDIA (New Delhi, India) _ Despite new ethnic bloodshed
in Kashmir and India's refusal to make significant concessions in
its nuclear weapons program, India's head of state sternly takes
President Clinton to task for repeatedly calling South Asia ``the
most dangerous place in the world.'' By CRAGG HINES.
</P>
