   POLITICAL NEWS (``p'' category)
</P>
<P>
   GORE-2000 (New York) _ Vice President Al Gore, a survivor of an
administration rocked by investigation, says he sees no need to
resurrect the independent counsel law. Gore also comments on the
government's proposed phaseout of the gasoline additive MTBE, soft
money and his opponent for the presidency, Texas Gov. George W.
Bush. By BENNETT ROTH.
</P>
<P>
   GORE-CENSUS (New York) _ Vice President Al Gore blasts Texas
Gov. George W. Bush for not supporting a method of counting that he
says would help the U.S. Census Bureau more accurately record
minorities. By BENNETT ROTH.
</P>
<P>
   McCAIN-RETURNS (Washington) _ Sen. John McCain makes his first
Senate speech after losing his maverick bid for the Republican
presidential nomination, talking about Kosovo to a throng of
tourists and reporters and columnists but virtually no other
senators. By JUDY HOLLAND. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-MCCAIN (Washington) _ George W. Bush and John McCain will
imperil Republicans' chances of retaking the White House and
keeping control of the House unless the two immediately end their
post-primary feud, says GOP pollster Frank Luntz. If they do, they
both should then go after the McCain supporters, many of whom,
according to Luntz, are drifting to Al Gore. By STEWART M. POWELL.
(Already filed.)
</P>
