   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CUBAN-BOY (Miami) _ A federal judge declines to block efforts to
return 6-year-old Elian Gonzalez to Cuba, saying only the U.S.
attorney general can grant political asylum in the United States.
U.S. District Judge K. Michael Moore's 50-page ruling dismisses the
lawsuit filed by the boy's great-uncle, Lazaro Gonzalez, who wants
the boy to remain in the United States. By ARMANDO VILLAFRANCA.
</P>
<P>
   CONDOMS-MEDICINE (Austin, Texas) _ A $160 million sales tax
break on over-the-counter medicines that begins April 1 will
include condoms, the Texas comptroller says. The decision
immediately drew fire. ``This is a terrible idea. The Legislature
did not intend for that tax exemption to be promoting promiscuity,
yet that's exactly what it's doing,'' says Cathie Adams, president
of the Texas Eagle Forum. By JOHN GONZALEZ.
</P>
