<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    The art of Texas
 &HT;    By Tom Sabulis
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   There are several new museum projects in Texas. The major
additions:
</P>
<P>
   AUSTIN
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Austin Museum of Art. Architect: Richard Gluckman. Cost: $60
million. Opening: 2003.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Jack S. Blanton Museum at the University of Texas. Architect:
TBA. Cost: $42 million. Opening: 2002.
</P>
<P>
   DALLAS
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Nasher Foundation sculpture garden (next to Dallas Museum of
Art). Architect: Renzo Piano. Cost: $32 million. Opening: 2001.
</P>
<P>
   FORT WORTH
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Modern Art Museum of Fort Worth. Architect: Tadao Ando. Cost:
$70 million. Opening: 2002.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Amon Carter Museum expansion. Architect: Philip Johnson. Cost:
$36 million. Opening: 2001.
</P>
<P>
   _Tom Sabulis writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
