and frail that he could easily be mistaken for 10 or 11. A recent
test shows he is HIV-positive. Having lost both his mother and the
woman he came to regard as an aunt to AIDS. he feels fortunate
because a local group pays for his school fees and uniform. His
aunt's sister allows him to remain in the house, where he has lived
the nine years since his mother's death. ``I want to be a soldier
and a teacher,'' he says about his future. (Seamus Conlan/The Cox
News Service)
