<P>
   (NYT48) WASHINGTON -- March 21, 2000 -- MCCAIN-SENATE-2 -- Sen.
John McCain returned to the Senate on Tuesday with a crowd of
reporters in tow, but most of his colleagues missed his first floor
speech. But instead of delivering condemnations of soft money in
Washington politics, the hallmarks of his unsuccessful race for the
Republican presidential nomination, McCain instead chose to talk
about his assessment of the NATO deployment in Kosovo. (Stephen
Crowley/The New York Times)
