<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ELIAN-TIMELINE22-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    A look at Elian's journey
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Here are some key dates in the
4-month-long international custody battle over 6-year-old Elian
Gonzalez:
</P>
<P>
   Nov. 25: Fishermen find Elian clinging to an inner tube three
miles off Fort Lauderdale after his mother and nine others perish
during a trip from Cuba in a motor boat.
</P>
<P>
   Nov. 26: U.S. immigration officials release Elian to his great
uncle, Lazaro Gonzalez of Miami, until the agency can determine his
immigration status.
</P>
<P>
   Nov. 27: In Cuba, Juan Miguel Gonzalez, Elian's father, demands
the return of his son.
</P>
<P>
   Dec. 10: Lazaro Gonzalez submits an application for political
asylum on Elian's behalf.
</P>
<P>
   Jan. 5: Doris Meissner, commissioner of the Immigration and
Naturalization Service, sends a letter to Elian's father, great
uncle and lawyers notifying them of the U.S. government's decision
that the boy ``belongs with his father'' and must be returned to
Cuba by Jan. 14.
</P>
<P>
   Jan. 6: Hundreds of Cuban-Americans block intersections and cut
off access to the Port of Miami in protest of the government's
decision to return Elian to Cuba.
</P>
<P>
   Jan. 7: Lazaro Gonzalez petitions for temporary custody of Elian
in a Florida state court.
</P>
<P>
   Jan. 10: The state court issues an order setting a March 6
hearing on the custody petition and instructing that Juan Miguel
Gonzalez be served with the pleadings.
</P>
<P>
   Jan. 19: Lazaro Gonzalez files a federal lawsuit to challenge
the INS ruling that Elian be returned to his father.
</P>
<P>
   Jan. 21-31: Elian's grandmothers arrive from Cuba for meetings
with U.S. Attorney General Janet Reno and sympathetic congressmen.
The trip includes a reunion between the grandmothers and Elian at
the Miami Beach home of Sister Jeanne O'Laughlin.
</P>
<P>
   March 21: U.S. District Judge K. Michael Moore dismisses
political asylum lawsuit filed Jan. 19.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
