<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ROCKWELL22-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Groom humor: Rockwell turns the joke on himself
 &HT;    By Lyle V. Harris
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Admit it, it was fun laughing at him.
</P>
<P>
   But last night at a Sandy Springs comedy club, the man who
became the butt of a nationally televised joke called ``Who Wants
to Marry a Multi-Millionaire?'' proved he could get also get people
to laugh with him.
</P>
<P>
   Since his doomed February nuptials to Darva Conger on the Fox
network, Rick Rockwell has embarked on a multi-city ``Annulment
Tour'' in hopes of invigorating his stand-up comedy career, and
retooling his image as a publicity-seeking fraud.
</P>
<P>
   Days after the show aired to an audience estimated at 22 million
viewers, published reports revealed that a former girlfriend had
once filed a restraining order against him, that his real name is
Rick Balkey, and that he apparently padded his bank account to get
on the show in the first place.
</P>
<P>
   But after one of the worst one-night stands in recorded history,
Rockwell's one-night stand in Atlanta demonstrated that he has far
more skill as a comic than he ever showed as a husband.
</P>
<P>
   His hourlong set was filled with sexual humor, observational
riffs, sight gags and spot-on Ross Perot imitations that kept the
audience of about 250 people laughing and hooting.
</P>
<P>
   ``How many people get shut out of their honeymoon?'' Rockwell
said, opening his hourlong set with some self-deprecating jibes.
``Now how many of you came home to 100 news trucks waiting to tell
the world you didn't (have sex) on your honeymoon?''
</P>
<P>
   The audience roared, and Rockwell whose toothy smile makes him
look like a baby shark, knew he was on a roll.
</P>
<P>
   Whenever the crowd got restless, which it did several times,
Rockwell returned to the scene of the slime.
</P>
<P>
   Pointing to three women who showed up in bridal gowns sitting in
the audience, Rockwell turned to them and said: ``That's a real
nightmare for me, three Darvas.''
</P>
<P>
   Several times he purposely mangled Conger's name from Darva to
larvae, like the insect. And although they haven't spoken since
Conger filed for an annulment just 36 hours after their televised
marriage, it's clear that Rockwell has been following her career
closely. Maybe too closely.
</P>
<P>
   Remarking on published reports that Conger was going to pose
nude in a men's magazine after losing her job, Rockwell cracked:
``I hope she does. I'd like too see her naked at least once before
we get this thing dissolved.''
</P>
<P>
   But in a pre-show interview, it was Rockwell who seemed exposed.
</P>
<P>
   The 43-year-old Californian portrayed himself as a sad clown who
was crying on the inside while laughing all the way to the bank.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm an emotional cork right now,'' he said in a telephone
interview. ``It's all been so unsettling.''
</P>
<P>
   When asked if there was any difference between marrying a
complete stranger who only wants him for his bank roll, Rockwell
said: ``When you hire a prostitute, you don't build a walk-in
closet for them in your house like I did for Darva.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
